  "prompt": "Does every dog has rabies?",
  "response": "No, not every dog has rabies. Rabies is a viral disease that is typically transmitted through the bite of an infected animal. While any mammal, including dogs, can contract rabies if they are bitten by an infected animal, the vast majority of dogs are not rabid. Vaccination is key in preventing rabies in domestic animals, and most pet owners have their dogs vaccinated against the disease. Regular vaccination and responsible pet ownership help keep both pets and people safe from rabies. If you suspect a dog may have rabies or if a dog bites you, it is important to seek medical advice and report the incident to local animal control authorities.",
